ring in 1913: the Carnegie International Commission of Inquiry and its Report on the Balkan Wars.\" ''First World War Studies'' 5.2 (2014): 147-162.\n* {{cite book |last1=Uyar |first1=Mesut |last2=Erickson |first2=Edward |title=A Military History of the Ottomans: From Osman to Atat\u00fcrk |year=2009 |publisher=Praeger Security International |location=Santa Barbara, CA |isbn=978-0-275-98876-0}}\n* {{cite book |first=Vladimir |last=Stojan\u010devi\u0107 |title=Prvi balkanski rat: okrugli sto povodom 75. godi\u0161njice 1912\u20131987, 28. i 29. oktobar 1987 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qgIXAQAAIAAJ |year=1991 |publisher=Srpska akademija nauka i umetnosti}}\n* {{cite book |last=Ratkovi\u0107 |first=Borislav |others=Istorijski institut JNA |title=Prvi balkanski rat 1912\u20131913: Operacije srpskih snaga |trans-title=First Balkan War 1912\u20131913: Operations of Serbian Forces |location=Belgrade |publisher=Vojnoistorijski Institut |year=1975 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FUTRAAAAMAAJ}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{Cite book |editor-last=Batakovi\u0107 |editor-first=Du\u0161an T. |editor-link=Du\u0161an T. Batakovi\u0107 |title=Histoire du peuple serbe |trans-title=History of the Serbian People |language=French |year=2005 |location=Lausanne |publisher=L\u2019Age d\u2019Homme |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a0jA_LdH6nsC |accessdate=}}\n* {{Cite book |last=\u0106irkovi\u0107 |first=Sima |authorlink=Sima \u0106irkovi\u0107 |title=The Serbs |year=2004 |location=Malden |publisher=Blackwell |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2Wc-DWRzoeIC |accessdate=}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Jelavich |first=Barbara |authorlink=Barbara Jelavich |title=History of the Balkans: Twentieth Century |volume=II |year=1983 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hd-or3qtqrsC |accessdate=}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{Commons category|First Balkan War}}\n{{Library resources box}}\n* Hall, Richard C.: [https://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online