{"title_page": "Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|De Tom\u00e1s|G\u00f3mez}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s\n| image = Real Valladolid - Rayo Vallecano 2019-01-05 20 (cropped) RDT.jpg\n| caption = De Tom\u00e1s with [[Rayo Vallecano]] in 2019\n| fullname = Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s G\u00f3mez\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|10|17|df=y}}<ref name=Bio>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/raul-de-tomas_prs327026/person.shtml|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], Spain<ref name=Bio/>\n| height = 1.78m<ref name=Bio/>\n| position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n| clubnumber = 11\n| youthyears1 = 2001\u20132004 | youthclubs1 = San Roque\n| youthyears2 = 2004\u20132013 | youthclubs2 = [[Real Madrid CF (youth)|Real Madrid]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[Real Madrid C]] | caps1 = 16 | goals1 = 8\n| years2 = 2013\u20132015 | clubs2 = [[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]] | caps2 = 62 | goals2 = 14\n| years3 = 2014\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] (loan) | caps4 = 26 | goals4 = 6\n| years5 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] (loan) | caps5 = 36 | goals5 = 14\n| years6 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Rayo Vallecano]] (loan) | caps6 = 65 | goals6 = 38\n| years7 = 2019\u20132020 | clubs7 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] | caps7 = 7 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2020\u2013 | clubs8 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] | caps8 = 6 | goals8 = 4\n| nationalyears1 = 2009 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-16 football team|Spain U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u20132011 | nationalteam2 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 6 | nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2012 | nationalteam3 = [[Spain national under-18 football team|Spain U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 2 | nationalgoals3 = 2\n| nationalyears4 = 2012\u20132013 | nationalteam4 = [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain U19]] | nationalcaps4 = 4 | nationalgoals4 = 2\n| club-update = 23:51, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s G\u00f3mez''' ({{IPA-es|ra\u02c8ul de to\u02c8maz \u02c8\u0263ome\u03b8}};{{efn|In isolation, ''Tom\u00e1s'' and ''G\u00f3mez'' are pronounced {{IPA-es|to\u02c8mas|}} and {{IPA-es|\u02c8\u0261ome\u03b8|}} respectively.}} born 17 October 1994) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[RCD Espanyol]] as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\nHe began as a youth team player at [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], but made only one [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] appearance for the first team but played and scored regularly on loans to [[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] and [[Rayo Vallecano]] of [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]], winning promotion to [[La Liga]] with the last of those teams. In 2019 he joined Portugal's [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] for a \u20ac20 million fee, returning to Spain's top flight with [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] six months later for the same price.\n\n==Club career==\n===Real Madrid===\n====Reserve teams====\nBorn in [[Madrid]] to a [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] mother,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariolibre.com/deportes/dominicano-debuta-con-el-real-madrid-GNDL721061|title=Dominicano debuta con el Real Madrid|trans-title=Dominican makes debut with Real Madrid|publisher=Diario Libre|first=Nathanael|last=P\u00e9rez Ner\u00f3|language=es|date=28 July 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> De Tom\u00e1s joined [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s youth academy in 2004 after starting out at CD San Roque EFF. He played his first senior match on 8 April 2012, featuring the last 21 minutes for [[Real Madrid C|the C-team]] in a 2\u20130 home win against [[CF Pozuelo de Alarc\u00f3n]] for the [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s was promoted to the third team in the middle of 2012, with the side now in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]]. On 17 August 2012 he appeared in his first game for [[Real Madrid Castilla|the reserves]], coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Juanfran (footballer, born 1988)|Juanfran]] in a 1\u20132 away loss to [[Villarreal CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2012/08/17/futbol/2adivision/1345237033.html|title=Cavenaghi toma los mandos del 'Submarino'|trans-title=Cavenaghi takes charge of the 'Submarine'|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|first=Diego|last=Acedo|language=es|date=17 August 2012|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 December, back with the C-side, De Tom\u00e1s scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 5\u20132 home rout of [[CD Marino]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensacentral.com/la_fabrica/78859-real-madrid-c-5-marino-de-luanco-2-segunda-division-b-raul-de-tomas-3-goles-cuarta-victoria-seguida-cerca-de-puestos-de-play-off/|title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s aniquil\u00f3 al Marino|trans-title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s annihilated Marino|publisher=Defensa Central|first=Miguel \u00c1ngel|last=D\u00edaz|language=es|date=16 December 2012|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He continued to represent both affiliates during the season, and was definitely promoted to Castilla in September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/09/03/futbol/equipos/castilla/1378235915.html|title=El Castilla se queda sin Henrique|trans-title=Castilla lose Henrique|newspaper=Marca|first=Emilio|last=Giraldo|language=es|date=3 September 2013|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s scored his first professional goal on 4 December 2013, netting the first in a 3\u20132 home victory over [[Girona FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/12/04/futbol/2adivision/1386190718.html|title=El Castilla ahuyenta fantasmas|trans-title=Castilla chase ghosts away|newspaper=Marca|first=Rub\u00e9n|last=Jim\u00e9nez|language=es|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He contributed with a further six in 27 appearances over [[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the campaign]], as the B-team suffered relegation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bernabeudigital.com/cantera/lucas-vazquez-el-pichichi-del-castilla-8592|title=Lucas V\u00e1zquez, el pichichi del Castilla|trans-title=Lucas V\u00e1zquez, Castilla's ''pichichi''|publisher=Bernab\u00e9u Digital|first=Leticia|last=Dom\u00ednguez|language=es|date=22 May 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2014, De Tom\u00e1s was included in the main squad for its pre-season trip to the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2014/07/ancelotti-cita-a-20-jugadores-para-viajar-a-ee-uu|title=Los 20 jugadores que inician el viaje a Estados Unidos|trans-title=The 20 players who start the trip to the United States|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=21 July 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for them on 29 October of the same year, replacing [[Karim Benzema]] in a [[2014\u201315 Copa del Rey|4\u20131 away defeat]] of [[UE Cornell\u00e0]] in the [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/copa/dieciseisavos/ida/cnr_rma/|title=Un ejercicio de profesionalidad|trans-title=An exercise in professionalism|newspaper=Marca|first=Delf\u00edn|last=Melero|language=es|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2014/10/raul-de-tomas-made-his-official-debut-with-real-madrid|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s made his official debut with Real Madrid|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Loans====\nOn 31 August 2015, De Tom\u00e1s was loaned to [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]] in a [[2014\u201315 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|season]]-long move.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/20150901/201483582662/el-cordoba-logra-la-cesion-del-delantero-raul-de-tomas-real-madrid-castilla.html|title=El C\u00f3rdoba logra la cesi\u00f3n del delantero Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s (Real Madrid Castilla)|trans-title=C\u00f3rdoba get loan of forward Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s (Real Madrid Castilla)|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=1 September 2015|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> Roughly one year later, he signed with [[Real Valladolid]] also in the second level and in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/31082016/Raul-de-Tomas-cierra-el-mercado/|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s cierra el mercado|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s closes the market|publisher=Real Valladolid|language=es|date=31 August 2016|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s was loaned to [[Rayo Vallecano]] on 1 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/raul-de-tomas-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano-2017-18|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano 2017\u201318|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s new player of Rayo Vallecano 2017\u201318|publisher=Rayo Vallecano|language=es|date=1 September 2017|accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref> He was the second-highest scorer of [[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the season]] with 24 goals, including hat-tricks in victories over [[Lorca FC]], [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]] and [[CF Reus Deportiu]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/deportes/futbol/abci-rayo-vallecano-lorca-liga-segunda-201801271701_directo.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s hunde al Lorca como colista|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s sinks Lorca into last place|newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=es|date=27 January 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180219/44928131276/raul-de-tomas-hay-que-ser-realistas-y-seguir-confiando.html|title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s: \"Hay que ser realistas y seguir confiando\"|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"We have to be realistic and maintain confidence\"|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=es|date=19 February 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.laopinion.es/deportes/2018/03/19/hat-trick-raul-tomas-coloca/860782.html|title=Un 'hat trick' de Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s coloca l\u00edder al Rayo Vallecano|trans-title=A Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s hat-trick puts Rayo Vallecano in first place|newspaper=[[La Opini\u00f3n de Tenerife]]|language=es|date=18 March 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> as the club from [[Vallecas]] won the league and were promoted back to the top flight; this haul was a season record for any player in its history,<ref name=Segunda>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180605/444131158946/raul-de-tomas-siempre-sere-del-rayito-como-lo-fui-de-nino.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"Siempre ser\u00e9 del Rayito, como lo fui de ni\u00f1o\"|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"I will always be a Rayito fan, like I was as a kid\"|newspaper=La Vanguardia|language=es|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> and he was also named [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Player of the Month]] in February and April 2018.<ref name=February>{{cite web|url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/raul-de-tomas-mejor-jugador-de-laliga-1l2l3-en-febrero|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, Mejor Jugador de LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 en febrero|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, best LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 player in February|publisher=[[La Liga]]|language=es|date=15 March 2018|accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref name=April>{{cite web|url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/raul-de-tomas-mejor-jugador-de-laliga-1l2l3-en-abril|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, Mejor Jugador de LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 en abril|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, best LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 player in April|publisher=La Liga|language=es|date=11 May 2018|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 June 2018, De Tom\u00e1s signed a new contract with Real Madrid until 2023. Two months later, he was loaned to Rayo Vallecano for [[2018\u201319 La Liga|another campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/raul-de-tomas-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano|publisher=Rayo Vallecano|language=es|date=24 August 2018|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-raul-de-tomas|title=Official announcement: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=24 August 2018|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal in the [[Spanish football league system|Spanish top tier]] on 22 September, but in a 1\u20135 home defeat against [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180922/451964442994/1-5-el-alaves-se-impone-con-comodidad-al-desproposito-del-rayo.html|title=1\u20135. El Alav\u00e9s se impone con comodidad al desprop\u00f3sito del Rayo|trans-title=1\u20135. Alav\u00e9s best Rayo disarray easily|newspaper=La Vanguardia|language=es|date=22 September 2018|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref> The following 11 January, also at the ''[[Campo de F\u00fatbol de Vallecas]]'', his hat-trick helped the hosts down [[RC Celta de Vigo]] 4\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/english/destacada/rayo-top-celta-4-2-on-de-tomas-hat-trick/50000261-3864746|title=Rayo top Celta 4\u20132 on De Tomas hat trick|publisher=[[EFE]]|date=12 January 2019|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\nOn 3 July 2019, De Tom\u00e1s signed a five-year contract with Portuguese champions [[S.L. Benfica]] on a \u20ac20 million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2019/07/03/futebol-benfica-raul-de-tomas-declaracoes-btv-reforco|title=Welcome, Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s!|publisher=S.L. Benfica|date=3 July 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-raul-de-tomas|title=Official announcement: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=3 July 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref> He debuted for the club as a starter in the [[2019 Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira|5\u20130 thrashing]] of [[Lisbon derby|crosstown rivals]] [[Sporting CP]] in the [[Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira]] on 4 August.<ref name=Debut>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1230-benfica-stick-five-past-sporting-in-season-curtain-raiser|title=Benfica stick five past Sporting in season curtain-raiser|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=4 August 2019|accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the side in a 1\u20123 loss at [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|the group stage]] of the [[UEFA Champions League]], as a substitute;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/10/03/zenit-grind-down-benfica-in-3-1-home-win|title=Zenit grind down Benfica in 3\u20131 home win|publisher=[[Euronews]]|date=3 October 2019|accessdate=7 November 2019}}</ref> [[UEFA]] ordered his shirt to say his legal surname for that match, while he habitually wore his initials instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/imposicao-da-uefa-obriga-benfica-a-mudar-o-nome-da-camisola-de-de-tomas|title=Imposi\u00e7\u00e3o da UEFA \"obriga\" Benfica a mudar o nome da camisola de De Tomas|trans-title=UEFA ruling \"forces\" Benfica to change the name on De Tomas's shirt|newspaper=[[Correio da Manh\u00e3]]|first1=Ant\u00f3nio M.|last1=Pereira|first2=Filipe Ant\u00f3nio|last2=Ferreira|language=pt|date=4 October 2019|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref> \n\nDuring his spell at the [[Est\u00e1dio da Luz]], De Tom\u00e1s scored only three goals from 17 appearances.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2020/01/07/chegou-por-20-milhoes-fez-1-042-minutos-em-17-jogos-nao-se-adaptou-saiu-por-22-milhoes-raul-de-tomas-no-espanyol/|title=Chegou por 20 milh\u00f5es, fez 1.042 minutos em 17 jogos, n\u00e3o se adaptou, saiu por 22 milh\u00f5es: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s no Espanyol|trans-title=He arrived for 20 million, totalled 1,042 minutes in 17 matches, failed to adapt, left for 22 million: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s to Espanyol|newspaper=Observador|first=Bruno|last=Roseiro|language=pt|date=7 January 2020|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=Espanyol>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2020/01/09/5e170594268e3ed2598b460b.html|title=Official: Raul de Tomas joins Espanyol from Benfica|newspaper=Marca|first1=Cristina|last1=Navarro|first2=Geoff|last2=Gillingham|date=9 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Espanyol===\nOn 9 January 2020, De Tom\u00e1s returned to his country's top flight, signing for [[RCD Espanyol]] on a contract lasting until 2026. The transfer fee of \u20ac20 million was a new record for the club from [[Barcelona]], nearly doubling the \u20ac10.5 million they paid for [[Mat\u00edas Vargas (footballer, born 1997)|Mat\u00edas Vargas]]; Benfica retained 20% of his future transfer fee.<ref name=Espanyol/> Three days after joining, he made his debut away to [[UD San Sebasti\u00e1n de los Reyes]] in the [[2019\u201320 Copa del Rey|third round of the national cup]], coming on in the 61st minute for [[Jonathan Calleri]] and wrapping up a 2\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/rcde-espanyol/primer-equipo/20200112/472848401723/espanyol-san-sebastian-de-los-reyes-resumen-copa-del-rey.html|title=De Tom\u00e1s ya golea para el Espanyol |trans-title=De Tom\u00e1s scores already for Espanyol|newspaper=La Vanguardia|first=Roberto|last=Rodr\u00edguez|language=es|date=12 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> On 19 January, he started in his first league game and scored the decisive goal of a 2\u20131 victory at [[Villarreal CF]];<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/cronica/2020/01/19/5e248db546163fd7728b456a.html|title=Espanyol hold on for crucial three points away at Villarreal|newspaper=Marca|first=Geoff|last=Gillingham|date=19 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> he scored in each of his first five games, triggering a clause that obliged Espanyol to pay Benfica a further \u20ac500,000.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/rcd-espanyol/20200210/473411636780/espanyol-de-tomas-goles-benfica-extra.html|title=Los cinco goles de Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s le cuestan al Espanyol 500.000 euros extras|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s' five goals cost Espanyol 500,000 euros more|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|first=Jaume|last=Miserachs|language=es|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDe Tom\u00e1s' father, also named Ra\u00fal (born 1967), was also a footballer and a [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. He spent most of his career in the Spanish third division.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://realvalladolid.elnortedecastilla.es/noticias/201610/02/raul-tomas-resiliencia-talento-20160927225549.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, resiliencia y talento|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, resilience and talent|newspaper=[[El Norte de Castilla]]|first=Arturo|last=Posada|language=es|date=2 October 2016|accessdate=29 June 2019}}</ref> His younger brother, Rub\u00e9n, came through the youth ranks of Rayo Vallecano.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ud-sanse.com/2019/08/ruben-de-tomas-nuevo-fichaje-de-la-u-d-sanse/|title=Rub\u00e9n de Tom\u00e1s, nuevo fichaje de la U. D. Sanse|trans-title=Rub\u00e9n de Tom\u00e1s, new signing for U. D. Sanse|publisher=UD S.S. Reyes|language=es|date=21 August 2019|accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|7 March 2020}}<ref>{{Soccerway|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{ForaDeJogo|199410170015}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Real Madrid C]]\n|2011\u201312\n|1||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2012\u201313]]\n|14||8\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||14||8\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2013\u201314]]\n|1||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n!Total\n!16!!8\n! colspan=\"6\" |\u2014!!16!!8\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2012\u201313]]\n|7||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||7||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2013\u201314]]\n|27||7\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||27||7\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2014\u201315]]\n|28||7\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||28||7\n|-\n!Total\n!62!!14\n! colspan=\"6\" |\u2014!!62!!14\n|-\n|[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]\n|[[2014\u201315 La Liga|2014\u201315]]\n|0||0\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] (loan)\n|[[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2015\u201316]]\n|26||6\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||27||6\n|-\n|[[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] (loan)\n|[[2016\u201317 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2016\u201317]]\n|36||14\n|2\n|1|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||38||15\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Rayo Vallecano]] (loan)\n|[[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2017\u201318]]\n|32||24\n|0\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||32||24\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 La Liga|2018\u201319]]\n|33||14\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||34||14\n|-\n!Total\n!65!!38!!1!!0!! colspan=\"4\" |\u2014!!66!!38\n|-\n|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2019-20 Primeira Liga|2019\u201320]]\n|7||0||2||1||3||1||4||1||16||3\n|-\n|[[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n|[[2019\u201320 RCD Espanyol season|2019\u201320]]\n|6||4||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||7||5\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!217!!83!!8!!3!!3!!1!!4!!1!!232!!88\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Rayo Vallecano'''\n*[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2017\u201318]]<ref name=Segunda/>\n\n'''Benfica'''\n*[[Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira]]: [[2019 Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira|2019]]<ref name=Debut/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Player of the Month]]: February 2018,<ref name=February/> April 2018<ref name=April/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of association football families]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol}}\n*{{UEFA player}}\n\n{{RCD Espanyol squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tomas, Raul De}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish people of Dominican Republic descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Madrid]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Madrilenian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid C footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid Castilla footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF players]]\n[[Category:C\u00f3rdoba CF players]]\n[[Category:Real Valladolid players]]\n[[Category:Rayo Vallecano players]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol footballers]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|De Tom\u00e1s|G\u00f3mez}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s\n| image = Real Valladolid - Rayo Vallecano 2019-01-05 20 (cropped) RDT.jpg\n| caption = De Tom\u00e1s with [[Rayo Vallecano]] in 2019\n| fullname = Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s G\u00f3mez\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|10|17|df=y}}<ref name=Bio>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/raul-de-tomas_prs327026/person.shtml|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], Spain<ref name=Bio/>\n| height = 1.78m<ref name=Bio/>\n| position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n| clubnumber = 11\n| youthyears1 = 2001\u20132004 | youthclubs1 = San Roque\n| youthyears2 = 2004\u20132013 | youthclubs2 = [[Real Madrid CF (youth)|Real Madrid]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[Real Madrid C]] | caps1 = 16 | goals1 = 8\n| years2 = 2013\u20132015 | clubs2 = [[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]] | caps2 = 62 | goals2 = 14\n| years3 = 2014\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] (loan) | caps4 = 26 | goals4 = 6\n| years5 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] (loan) | caps5 = 36 | goals5 = 14\n| years6 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Rayo Vallecano]] (loan) | caps6 = 65 | goals6 = 38\n| years7 = 2019\u20132020 | clubs7 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] | caps7 = 7 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2020\u2013 | clubs8 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] | caps8 = 6 | goals8 = 4\n| nationalyears1 = 2009 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-16 football team|Spain U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u20132011 | nationalteam2 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 6 | nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2012 | nationalteam3 = [[Spain national under-18 football team|Spain U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 2 | nationalgoals3 = 2\n| nationalyears4 = 2012\u20132013 | nationalteam4 = [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain U19]] | nationalcaps4 = 4 | nationalgoals4 = 2\n| club-update = 23:51, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s G\u00f3mez''' ({{IPA-es|ra\u02c8ul de to\u02c8maz \u02c8\u0263ome\u03b8}};{{efn|In isolation, ''Tom\u00e1s'' and ''G\u00f3mez'' are pronounced {{IPA-es|to\u02c8mas|}} and {{IPA-es|\u02c8\u0261ome\u03b8|}} respectively.}} born 17 October 1994) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[RCD Espanyol]] as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\nHe began as a youth team player at [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]. He made only one [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] appearance for the first team but played and scored regularly on loans to [[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] and [[Rayo Vallecano]] of [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]], winning promotion to [[La Liga]] with the last of those teams. In 2019 he joined Portugal's [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] for a \u20ac20 million fee, returning to Spain's top flight with [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] six months later for the same price.\n\n==Club career==\n===Real Madrid===\n====Reserve teams====\nBorn in [[Madrid]] to a [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] mother,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariolibre.com/deportes/dominicano-debuta-con-el-real-madrid-GNDL721061|title=Dominicano debuta con el Real Madrid|trans-title=Dominican makes debut with Real Madrid|publisher=Diario Libre|first=Nathanael|last=P\u00e9rez Ner\u00f3|language=es|date=28 July 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> De Tom\u00e1s joined [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s youth academy in 2004 after starting out at CD San Roque EFF. He played his first senior match on 8 April 2012, featuring the last 21 minutes for [[Real Madrid C|the C-team]] in a 2\u20130 home win against [[CF Pozuelo de Alarc\u00f3n]] for the [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s was promoted to the third team in the middle of 2012, with the side now in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]]. On 17 August 2012 he appeared in his first game for [[Real Madrid Castilla|the reserves]], coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Juanfran (footballer, born 1988)|Juanfran]] in a 1\u20132 away loss to [[Villarreal CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2012/08/17/futbol/2adivision/1345237033.html|title=Cavenaghi toma los mandos del 'Submarino'|trans-title=Cavenaghi takes charge of the 'Submarine'|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|first=Diego|last=Acedo|language=es|date=17 August 2012|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 December, back with the C-side, De Tom\u00e1s scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 5\u20132 home rout of [[CD Marino]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensacentral.com/la_fabrica/78859-real-madrid-c-5-marino-de-luanco-2-segunda-division-b-raul-de-tomas-3-goles-cuarta-victoria-seguida-cerca-de-puestos-de-play-off/|title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s aniquil\u00f3 al Marino|trans-title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s annihilated Marino|publisher=Defensa Central|first=Miguel \u00c1ngel|last=D\u00edaz|language=es|date=16 December 2012|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He continued to represent both affiliates during the season, and was definitely promoted to Castilla in September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/09/03/futbol/equipos/castilla/1378235915.html|title=El Castilla se queda sin Henrique|trans-title=Castilla lose Henrique|newspaper=Marca|first=Emilio|last=Giraldo|language=es|date=3 September 2013|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s scored his first professional goal on 4 December 2013, netting the first in a 3\u20132 home victory over [[Girona FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/12/04/futbol/2adivision/1386190718.html|title=El Castilla ahuyenta fantasmas|trans-title=Castilla chase ghosts away|newspaper=Marca|first=Rub\u00e9n|last=Jim\u00e9nez|language=es|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He contributed with a further six in 27 appearances over [[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the campaign]], as the B-team suffered relegation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bernabeudigital.com/cantera/lucas-vazquez-el-pichichi-del-castilla-8592|title=Lucas V\u00e1zquez, el pichichi del Castilla|trans-title=Lucas V\u00e1zquez, Castilla's ''pichichi''|publisher=Bernab\u00e9u Digital|first=Leticia|last=Dom\u00ednguez|language=es|date=22 May 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2014, De Tom\u00e1s was included in the main squad for its pre-season trip to the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2014/07/ancelotti-cita-a-20-jugadores-para-viajar-a-ee-uu|title=Los 20 jugadores que inician el viaje a Estados Unidos|trans-title=The 20 players who start the trip to the United States|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=21 July 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for them on 29 October of the same year, replacing [[Karim Benzema]] in a [[2014\u201315 Copa del Rey|4\u20131 away defeat]] of [[UE Cornell\u00e0]] in the [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/copa/dieciseisavos/ida/cnr_rma/|title=Un ejercicio de profesionalidad|trans-title=An exercise in professionalism|newspaper=Marca|first=Delf\u00edn|last=Melero|language=es|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2014/10/raul-de-tomas-made-his-official-debut-with-real-madrid|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s made his official debut with Real Madrid|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Loans====\nOn 31 August 2015, De Tom\u00e1s was loaned to [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]] in a [[2014\u201315 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|season]]-long move.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/20150901/201483582662/el-cordoba-logra-la-cesion-del-delantero-raul-de-tomas-real-madrid-castilla.html|title=El C\u00f3rdoba logra la cesi\u00f3n del delantero Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s (Real Madrid Castilla)|trans-title=C\u00f3rdoba get loan of forward Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s (Real Madrid Castilla)|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=1 September 2015|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> Roughly one year later, he signed with [[Real Valladolid]] also in the second level and in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/31082016/Raul-de-Tomas-cierra-el-mercado/|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s cierra el mercado|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s closes the market|publisher=Real Valladolid|language=es|date=31 August 2016|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nDe Tom\u00e1s was loaned to [[Rayo Vallecano]] on 1 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/raul-de-tomas-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano-2017-18|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano 2017\u201318|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s new player of Rayo Vallecano 2017\u201318|publisher=Rayo Vallecano|language=es|date=1 September 2017|accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref> He was the second-highest scorer of [[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the season]] with 24 goals, including hat-tricks in victories over [[Lorca FC]], [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]] and [[CF Reus Deportiu]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/deportes/futbol/abci-rayo-vallecano-lorca-liga-segunda-201801271701_directo.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s hunde al Lorca como colista|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s sinks Lorca into last place|newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=es|date=27 January 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180219/44928131276/raul-de-tomas-hay-que-ser-realistas-y-seguir-confiando.html|title=Ra\u00fal De Tom\u00e1s: \"Hay que ser realistas y seguir confiando\"|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"We have to be realistic and maintain confidence\"|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=es|date=19 February 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.laopinion.es/deportes/2018/03/19/hat-trick-raul-tomas-coloca/860782.html|title=Un 'hat trick' de Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s coloca l\u00edder al Rayo Vallecano|trans-title=A Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s hat-trick puts Rayo Vallecano in first place|newspaper=[[La Opini\u00f3n de Tenerife]]|language=es|date=18 March 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> as the club from [[Vallecas]] won the league and were promoted back to the top flight; this haul was a season record for any player in its history,<ref name=Segunda>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180605/444131158946/raul-de-tomas-siempre-sere-del-rayito-como-lo-fui-de-nino.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"Siempre ser\u00e9 del Rayito, como lo fui de ni\u00f1o\"|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s: \"I will always be a Rayito fan, like I was as a kid\"|newspaper=La Vanguardia|language=es|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> and he was also named [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Player of the Month]] in February and April 2018.<ref name=February>{{cite web|url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/raul-de-tomas-mejor-jugador-de-laliga-1l2l3-en-febrero|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, Mejor Jugador de LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 en febrero|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, best LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 player in February|publisher=[[La Liga]]|language=es|date=15 March 2018|accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref name=April>{{cite web|url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/raul-de-tomas-mejor-jugador-de-laliga-1l2l3-en-abril|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, Mejor Jugador de LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 en abril|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, best LaLiga 1{{!}}2{{!}}3 player in April|publisher=La Liga|language=es|date=11 May 2018|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 June 2018, De Tom\u00e1s signed a new contract with Real Madrid until 2023. Two months later, he was loaned to Rayo Vallecano for [[2018\u201319 La Liga|another campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/raul-de-tomas-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano|publisher=Rayo Vallecano|language=es|date=24 August 2018|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-raul-de-tomas|title=Official announcement: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=24 August 2018|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal in the [[Spanish football league system|Spanish top tier]] on 22 September, but in a 1\u20135 home defeat against [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20180922/451964442994/1-5-el-alaves-se-impone-con-comodidad-al-desproposito-del-rayo.html|title=1\u20135. El Alav\u00e9s se impone con comodidad al desprop\u00f3sito del Rayo|trans-title=1\u20135. Alav\u00e9s best Rayo disarray easily|newspaper=La Vanguardia|language=es|date=22 September 2018|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref> The following 11 January, also at the ''[[Campo de F\u00fatbol de Vallecas]]'', his hat-trick helped the hosts down [[RC Celta de Vigo]] 4\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/english/destacada/rayo-top-celta-4-2-on-de-tomas-hat-trick/50000261-3864746|title=Rayo top Celta 4\u20132 on De Tomas hat trick|publisher=[[EFE]]|date=12 January 2019|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\nOn 3 July 2019, De Tom\u00e1s signed a five-year contract with Portuguese champions [[S.L. Benfica]] on a \u20ac20 million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2019/07/03/futebol-benfica-raul-de-tomas-declaracoes-btv-reforco|title=Welcome, Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s!|publisher=S.L. Benfica|date=3 July 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-raul-de-tomas|title=Official announcement: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=3 July 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref> He debuted for the club as a starter in the [[2019 Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira|5\u20130 thrashing]] of [[Lisbon derby|crosstown rivals]] [[Sporting CP]] in the [[Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira]] on 4 August.<ref name=Debut>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1230-benfica-stick-five-past-sporting-in-season-curtain-raiser|title=Benfica stick five past Sporting in season curtain-raiser|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=4 August 2019|accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the side in a 1\u20123 loss at [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|the group stage]] of the [[UEFA Champions League]], as a substitute;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/10/03/zenit-grind-down-benfica-in-3-1-home-win|title=Zenit grind down Benfica in 3\u20131 home win|publisher=[[Euronews]]|date=3 October 2019|accessdate=7 November 2019}}</ref> [[UEFA]] ordered his shirt to say his legal surname for that match, while he habitually wore his initials instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/imposicao-da-uefa-obriga-benfica-a-mudar-o-nome-da-camisola-de-de-tomas|title=Imposi\u00e7\u00e3o da UEFA \"obriga\" Benfica a mudar o nome da camisola de De Tomas|trans-title=UEFA ruling \"forces\" Benfica to change the name on De Tomas's shirt|newspaper=[[Correio da Manh\u00e3]]|first1=Ant\u00f3nio M.|last1=Pereira|first2=Filipe Ant\u00f3nio|last2=Ferreira|language=pt|date=4 October 2019|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref> \n\nDuring his spell at the [[Est\u00e1dio da Luz]], De Tom\u00e1s scored only three goals from 17 appearances.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2020/01/07/chegou-por-20-milhoes-fez-1-042-minutos-em-17-jogos-nao-se-adaptou-saiu-por-22-milhoes-raul-de-tomas-no-espanyol/|title=Chegou por 20 milh\u00f5es, fez 1.042 minutos em 17 jogos, n\u00e3o se adaptou, saiu por 22 milh\u00f5es: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s no Espanyol|trans-title=He arrived for 20 million, totalled 1,042 minutes in 17 matches, failed to adapt, left for 22 million: Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s to Espanyol|newspaper=Observador|first=Bruno|last=Roseiro|language=pt|date=7 January 2020|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=Espanyol>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2020/01/09/5e170594268e3ed2598b460b.html|title=Official: Raul de Tomas joins Espanyol from Benfica|newspaper=Marca|first1=Cristina|last1=Navarro|first2=Geoff|last2=Gillingham|date=9 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Espanyol===\nOn 9 January 2020, De Tom\u00e1s returned to his country's top flight, signing for [[RCD Espanyol]] on a contract lasting until 2026. The transfer fee of \u20ac20 million was a new record for the club from [[Barcelona]], nearly doubling the \u20ac10.5 million they paid for [[Mat\u00edas Vargas (footballer, born 1997)|Mat\u00edas Vargas]]; Benfica retained 20% of his future transfer fee.<ref name=Espanyol/> Three days after joining, he made his debut away to [[UD San Sebasti\u00e1n de los Reyes]] in the [[2019\u201320 Copa del Rey|third round of the national cup]], coming on in the 61st minute for [[Jonathan Calleri]] and wrapping up a 2\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/rcde-espanyol/primer-equipo/20200112/472848401723/espanyol-san-sebastian-de-los-reyes-resumen-copa-del-rey.html|title=De Tom\u00e1s ya golea para el Espanyol |trans-title=De Tom\u00e1s scores already for Espanyol|newspaper=La Vanguardia|first=Roberto|last=Rodr\u00edguez|language=es|date=12 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> On 19 January, he started in his first league game and scored the decisive goal of a 2\u20131 victory at [[Villarreal CF]];<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/cronica/2020/01/19/5e248db546163fd7728b456a.html|title=Espanyol hold on for crucial three points away at Villarreal|newspaper=Marca|first=Geoff|last=Gillingham|date=19 January 2020|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> he scored in each of his first five games, triggering a clause that obliged Espanyol to pay Benfica a further \u20ac500,000.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/rcd-espanyol/20200210/473411636780/espanyol-de-tomas-goles-benfica-extra.html|title=Los cinco goles de Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s le cuestan al Espanyol 500.000 euros extras|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s' five goals cost Espanyol 500,000 euros more|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|first=Jaume|last=Miserachs|language=es|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDe Tom\u00e1s' father, also named Ra\u00fal (born 1967), was also a footballer and a [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. He spent most of his career in the Spanish third division.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://realvalladolid.elnortedecastilla.es/noticias/201610/02/raul-tomas-resiliencia-talento-20160927225549.html|title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, resiliencia y talento|trans-title=Ra\u00fal de Tom\u00e1s, resilience and talent|newspaper=[[El Norte de Castilla]]|first=Arturo|last=Posada|language=es|date=2 October 2016|accessdate=29 June 2019}}</ref> His younger brother, Rub\u00e9n, came through the youth ranks of Rayo Vallecano.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ud-sanse.com/2019/08/ruben-de-tomas-nuevo-fichaje-de-la-u-d-sanse/|title=Rub\u00e9n de Tom\u00e1s, nuevo fichaje de la U. D. Sanse|trans-title=Rub\u00e9n de Tom\u00e1s, new signing for U. D. Sanse|publisher=UD S.S. Reyes|language=es|date=21 August 2019|accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|7 March 2020}}<ref>{{Soccerway|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{ForaDeJogo|199410170015}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Real Madrid C]]\n|2011\u201312\n|1||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2012\u201313]]\n|14||8\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||14||8\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2013\u201314]]\n|1||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n!Total\n!16!!8\n! colspan=\"6\" |\u2014!!16!!8\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2012\u201313]]\n|7||0\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||7||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2013\u201314]]\n|27||7\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||27||7\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2014\u201315]]\n|28||7\n| colspan=\"6\" |\u2014||28||7\n|-\n!Total\n!62!!14\n! colspan=\"6\" |\u2014!!62!!14\n|-\n|[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]\n|[[2014\u201315 La Liga|2014\u201315]]\n|0||0\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[C\u00f3rdoba CF|C\u00f3rdoba]] (loan)\n|[[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2015\u201316]]\n|26||6\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||27||6\n|-\n|[[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] (loan)\n|[[2016\u201317 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2016\u201317]]\n|36||14\n|2\n|1|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||38||15\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Rayo Vallecano]] (loan)\n|[[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2017\u201318]]\n|32||24\n|0\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||32||24\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 La Liga|2018\u201319]]\n|33||14\n|1\n|0|| colspan=\"4\" |\u2014||34||14\n|-\n!Total\n!65!!38!!1!!0!! colspan=\"4\" |\u2014!!66!!38\n|-\n|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2019-20 Primeira Liga|2019\u201320]]\n|7||0||2||1||3||1||4||1||16||3\n|-\n|[[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n|[[2019\u201320 RCD Espanyol season|2019\u201320]]\n|6||4||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||7||5\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!217!!83!!8!!3!!3!!1!!4!!1!!232!!88\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Rayo Vallecano'''\n*[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2017\u201318 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2017\u201318]]<ref name=Segunda/>\n\n'''Benfica'''\n*[[Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira]]: [[2019 Superta\u00e7a C\u00e2ndido de Oliveira|2019]]<ref name=Debut/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Player of the Month]]: February 2018,<ref name=February/> April 2018<ref name=April/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of association football families]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol}}\n*{{UEFA player}}\n\n{{RCD Espanyol squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tomas, Raul De}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish people of Dominican Republic descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Madrid]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Madrilenian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid C footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid Castilla footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF players]]\n[[Category:C\u00f3rdoba CF players]]\n[[Category:Real Valladolid players]]\n[[Category:Rayo Vallecano players]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol footballers]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n", "name_user": "Quite A Character", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor intro tweak.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ra%C3%BAl_de_Tom%C3%A1s"}
{"title_page": "Edit-a-thon", "text_new": "{{short description|Term to describe a wiki's in-person editing collaboration on a specific topic}}\n{{For|details of Wikipedia edit-a-thons|Wikipedia:How to run an edit-a-thon|selfref=yes}}\n[[File:Editat\u00f3n 72HorasConRodin - S\u00e1bado - 35.jpg|thumb|The ''72 horas con Rodin'' edit-a-thon in Mexico City is the longest ever held, recognized by [[Guinness World Records]].]]\n[[File:Giants in the field of Women in the Arts 2.jpg|thumb|Attendees at the 2013 Women in the Arts Edit-a-thon in Washington, DC]]\n[[File:Editathon das minas.jpg|thumb|An edit-a-thon in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]], aimed at creating and improving Wikipedia articles relating to [[feminism]], [[women's rights]] and notable women]]\n[[File:What-is-an-edit-a-thon-sherry-antoine.mp3|thumb|[[AfroCrowd]] Manager Sherry Antoine explaining edit-a-thons]]\nAn '''edit-a-thon''' (sometimes written '''editathon''') is an organized event where editors of [[online community|online communities]] such as [[Wikipedia]], [[OpenStreetMap]], and [[LocalWiki]]  edit and improve a specific topic or type of content, typically including basic editing training for new editors. They often involve meetups, but can be distributed as well. The word is a [[portmanteau]] of \"edit\" and \"[[marathon]]\".\n\nWikipedia edit-a-thons have taken place at [[Wikimedia chapter]] headquarters; accredited educational institutions, including [[Sonoma State University]], [[Arizona State University]], [[Middlebury College]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.middlebury.edu/newsroom/archive/2017-news/node/547035|title=Feminists Strengthen Wikipedia's Content about Women|date=April 18, 2017|website=Middlebury College|access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> and the [[University of Victoria]]; scientific research institutions such as the [[Salk Institute for Biological Studies|Salk Institute for Biological Sciences]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.salk.edu/events/wikipedia-edit-a-thon/|title=Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon - September 7, 2019|website=Salk Institute for Biological Studies|language=en|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref>; and [[cultural institutions]], such as [[museums]] or [[archives]]. The events have included topics such as cultural heritage sites, museum collections, [[women's history]], art, feminism, narrowing [[Gender bias on Wikipedia|Wikipedia's gender gap]], and [[social justice]] issues.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newyorker.com/tech/elements/a-feminist-edit-a-thon-seeks-to-reshape-wikipedia|title=A Feminist Edit-a-Thon Seeks to Reshape Wikipedia|last=Lavin|first=Talia|date=2016-03-11|newspaper=The New Yorker|issn=0028-792X|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/15/wikipedia-gender-racial-bias_n_7054550.html|title=Editors Are Trying To Fix Wikipedia's Gender And Racial Bias Problem|last=Content|first=Sara Boboltz Associate Editor of Viral|last2=Post|first2=The Huffington|date=2015-04-15|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uvic.ca/library/home/home/news/current/social-justice-wikipedia-edit-a-thon-workshop.php|title=Social Justice Wikipedia Edit-a-thon workshop - University of Victoria|website=www.uvic.ca|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abqjournal.com/283040/female-scientists-getting-their-due-on-wikipedia.html|title=Female scientists getting their due on Wikipedia|last=Smith|first=Michelle R.|date=16 October 2013|work=|newspaper=Associated Press|access-date=2016-07-30|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/2014/02/01/scsu-group-participates-in-edit-a-thon-for-wikipedia-website-/5123333/|title=SCSU group participates in edit-a-thon for Wikipedia website|last=Katzner|first=Ben|date=1 February 2014|newspaper=[[St. Cloud Times]]|accessdate=5 February 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160802121102/http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/2014/02/01/scsu-group-participates-in-edit-a-thon-for-wikipedia-website-/5123333/|archivedate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Koh|first=Adeline|title=How to Organize Your Own Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon|url=http://chronicle.com/blogs/profhacker/how-to-organize-your-own-wikipedia-edit-a-thon/49757|accessdate=5 February 2014|newspaper=[[The Chronicle of Higher Education]]|date=30 May 2013}}</ref> Women, African Americans, and members of the [[LGBT community]] are using edit-a-thons to bridge the gap in Wikipedia's sexual and racial makeup<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reynosa|first1=Peter|title=Why Don't More Latinos Contribute to Wikipedia?|url=http://eltecolote.org/content/en/commentary/why-dont-more-latinos-contribute-to-wikipedia/|publisher=El Tecolote|accessdate=December 4, 2015}}</ref> and to challenge the underrepresentation of Africa-related topics.<ref>Wexelbaum, Rachel S., Katie Herzog, and Lane Rasberry. \"Queering Wikipedia.\" (2015).</ref>\n\nSome have been organized by [[Wikipedian in residence|Wikipedians in residence]]. The longest edit-a-thon took place at the [[Museo Soumaya]] in [[Mexico City]] from June 9 to 12, 2016, where [[Wikipedia:Wikimedia M\u00e9xico|Wikimedia Mexico]] volunteers and museum's staff edited during 72 continuous hours. The record was recognized by [[Guinness World Records]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dineroenimagen.com/2016-06-13/74222|title=M\u00e9xico gan\u00f3 un nuevo r\u00e9cord Guinness y seguro te va a ser \u00fatil|website=Dinero en Imagen.com|language=es-MX|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.wikimedia.org/2016/07/22/mexico-soumaya-rodin/|title=Wikipedia edit-a-thon, 72 hours long, is recognized with a Guinness World Record|last=Cruz y Corro|first=Andr\u00e9s|last2=Fernanda L\u00f3pez|first2=Mar\u00eda|date=22 July 2016|website=Wikimedia Blog|publisher=|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref> The OpenStreetMap community has also hosted several edit-a-thons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mapbox.com/blog/spring-openstreetmap-editathon/ |title=OpenStreetMap #Editathon at MapBox |date=12 April 2013 |first=Ian |last=Villeda |accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dusp.mit.edu/uis/event/fall-2013-openstreetmap-editathon |title=Fall 2013 OpenStreetMap Editathon |last=Foster |first=Mike |date=18 October 2013 |accessdate=7 April 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408223530/http://dusp.mit.edu/uis/event/fall-2013-openstreetmap-editathon |archivedate=8 April 2014 }}</ref> In August 2018, [https://www.futureclimateafrica.org/ Future Climate for Africa] and the [https://cdkn.org/?loclang=en_gb Climate and Development Knowledge Network] convened the first [[metawiki:African_Climate_Change_edit-a-thon|African Wikipedia edit-a-thon on climate change]] in Cape Town South Africa. \n\nSince 2014, [[Art+Feminism]] has held world-wide edit-a-thons annually to expand the histories of women, feminism, and arts found on Wikipedia, and to dismantle the biases on how women are represented online. 2019 marks the expansion of the movement to include \"gender non-binary activists and artists\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artandfeminism.tumblr.com/post/181023341915/announcing-our-year-6-campaign-gender-the|title=ART+FEMINISM \u2014 Announcing Our Year 6 Campaign: Gender + The...|website=ART+FEMINISM|language=en|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Hackathon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Wikimedia edit-a-thons}}\n* [https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Mapathon OpenStreetMap 'Mapathons']\n\n{{Wikipedia}}\n\n[[Category:Activism by type]]\n[[Category:OpenStreetMap]]\n[[Category:Wikipedia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Term to describe a wiki's in-person editing collaboration on a specific topic}}\n{{For|details of Wikipedia edit-a-thons|Wikipedia:How to run an edit-a-thon|selfref=yes}}\n[[File:Editat\u00f3n 72HorasConRodin - S\u00e1bado - 35.jpg|thumb|The ''72 horas con Rodin'' edit-a-thon in Mexico City is the longest ever held, recognized by [[Guinness World Records]].]]\n[[File:Giants in the field of Women in the Arts 2.jpg|thumb|Attendees at the 2013 Women in the Arts Edit-a-thon in Washington, DC]]\n[[File:Editathon das minas.jpg|thumb|An edit-a-thon in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]], aimed at creating and improving Wikipedia articles relating to [[feminism]], [[women's rights]] and notable women]]\n[[File:What-is-an-edit-a-thon-sherry-antoine.mp3|thumb|[[AfroCrowd]] Manager Sherry Antoine explaining edit-a-thons]]\nAn '''edit-a-thon''' (sometimes written '''editathon''') is an organized event where editors of [[online community|online communities]] such as [[Wikipedia]], [[OpenStreetMap]], and [[LocalWiki]]  edit and improve a specific topic or type of content, typically including basic editing training for new editors. They often involve meetups, but can be distributed as well. The word is a [[portmanteau]] of \"edit\" and \"[[marathon]]\".\n\nWikipedia edit-a-thons have taken place at [[Wikimedia chapter]] headquarters; accredited educational institutions, including [[Sonoma State University]], [[Arizona State University]], [[Middlebury College]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.middlebury.edu/newsroom/archive/2017-news/node/547035|title=Feminists Strengthen Wikipedia's Content about Women|date=April 18, 2017|website=Middlebury College|access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> and the [[University of Victoria]]; scientific research institutions such as the [[Salk Institute for Biological Studies|Salk Institute for Biological Sciences]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.salk.edu/events/wikipedia-edit-a-thon/|title=Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon - September 7, 2019|website=Salk Institute for Biological Studies|language=en|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref>; and [[cultural institutions]], such as [[museums]] or [[archives]]. The events have included topics such as cultural heritage sites, museum collections, [[women's history]], art, feminism, narrowing [[Gender bias on Wikipedia|Wikipedia's gender gap]], and [[social justice]] issues.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newyorker.com/tech/elements/a-feminist-edit-a-thon-seeks-to-reshape-wikipedia|title=A Feminist Edit-a-Thon Seeks to Reshape Wikipedia|last=Lavin|first=Talia|date=2016-03-11|newspaper=The New Yorker|issn=0028-792X|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/15/wikipedia-gender-racial-bias_n_7054550.html|title=Editors Are Trying To Fix Wikipedia's Gender And Racial Bias Problem|last=Content|first=Sara Boboltz Associate Editor of Viral|last2=Post|first2=The Huffington|date=2015-04-15|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uvic.ca/library/home/home/news/current/social-justice-wikipedia-edit-a-thon-workshop.php|title=Social Justice Wikipedia Edit-a-thon workshop - University of Victoria|website=www.uvic.ca|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abqjournal.com/283040/female-scientists-getting-their-due-on-wikipedia.html|title=Female scientists getting their due on Wikipedia|last=Smith|first=Michelle R.|date=16 October 2013|work=|newspaper=Associated Press|access-date=2016-07-30|via=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/2014/02/01/scsu-group-participates-in-edit-a-thon-for-wikipedia-website-/5123333/|title=SCSU group participates in edit-a-thon for Wikipedia website|last=Katzner|first=Ben|date=1 February 2014|newspaper=[[St. Cloud Times]]|accessdate=5 February 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160802121102/http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/2014/02/01/scsu-group-participates-in-edit-a-thon-for-wikipedia-website-/5123333/|archivedate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Koh|first=Adeline|title=How to Organize Your Own Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon|url=http://chronicle.com/blogs/profhacker/how-to-organize-your-own-wikipedia-edit-a-thon/49757|accessdate=5 February 2014|newspaper=[[The Chronicle of Higher Education]]|date=30 May 2013}}</ref> Women, African Americans, and members of the [[LGBT community]] are using edit-a-thons to bridge the gap in Wikipedia's sexual and racial makeup<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reynosa|first1=Peter|title=Why Don't More Latinos Contribute to Wikipedia?|url=http://eltecolote.org/content/en/commentary/why-dont-more-latinos-contribute-to-wikipedia/|publisher=El Tecolote|accessdate=December 4, 2015}}</ref> and to challenge the underrepresentation of Africa-related topics.<ref>Wexelbaum, Rachel S., Katie Herzog, and Lane Rasberry. \"Queering Wikipedia.\" (2015).</ref>\n\nSome have been organised by [[Wikipedian in residence|Wikipedians in residence]]. The longest edit-a-thon took place at the [[Museo Soumaya]] in [[Mexico City]] from June 9 to 12, 2016, where [[Wikipedia:Wikimedia M\u00e9xico|Wikimedia Mexico]] volunteers and museum's staff edited during 72 continuous hours. The record was recognized by [[Guinness World Records]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dineroenimagen.com/2016-06-13/74222|title=M\u00e9xico gan\u00f3 un nuevo r\u00e9cord Guinness y seguro te va a ser \u00fatil|website=Dinero en Imagen.com|language=es-MX|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.wikimedia.org/2016/07/22/mexico-soumaya-rodin/|title=Wikipedia edit-a-thon, 72 hours long, is recognized with a Guinness World Record|last=Cruz y Corro|first=Andr\u00e9s|last2=Fernanda L\u00f3pez|first2=Mar\u00eda|date=22 July 2016|website=Wikimedia Blog|publisher=|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref> The OpenStreetMap community has also hosted several edit-a-thons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mapbox.com/blog/spring-openstreetmap-editathon/ |title=OpenStreetMap #Editathon at MapBox |date=12 April 2013 |first=Ian |last=Villeda |accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dusp.mit.edu/uis/event/fall-2013-openstreetmap-editathon |title=Fall 2013 OpenStreetMap Editathon |last=Foster |first=Mike |date=18 October 2013 |accessdate=7 April 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408223530/http://dusp.mit.edu/uis/event/fall-2013-openstreetmap-editathon |archivedate=8 April 2014 }}</ref> In August 2018, [https://www.futureclimateafrica.org/ Future Climate for Africa] and the [https://cdkn.org/?loclang=en_gb Climate and Development Knowledge Network] convened the first [[metawiki:African_Climate_Change_edit-a-thon|African Wikipedia edit-a-thon on climate change]] in Cape Town South Africa. \n\nSince 2014, [[Art+Feminism]] has held world-wide edit-a-thons annually to expand the histories of women, feminism, and arts found on Wikipedia, and to dismantle the biases on how women are represented online. 2019 marks the expansion of the movement to include \"gender non-binary activists and artists\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artandfeminism.tumblr.com/post/181023341915/announcing-our-year-6-campaign-gender-the|title=ART+FEMINISM \u2014 Announcing Our Year 6 Campaign: Gender + The...|website=ART+FEMINISM|language=en|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Hackathon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Wikimedia edit-a-thons}}\n* [https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Mapathon OpenStreetMap 'Mapathons']\n\n{{Wikipedia}}\n\n[[Category:Activism by type]]\n[[Category:OpenStreetMap]]\n[[Category:Wikipedia]]\n", "name_user": "TheSameGuy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:The rest of the article was already using the US spelling.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edit-a-thon"}
{"title_page": "Jake Picking", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jake Picking\n| image              =\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1991|3|2}}\n| birth_place        = [[Erlangen, Germany]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present\n| girlfriend(s)      = Fiona Barron\n}}\n\n'''Jake Picking''' (born March 2, 1991) is an American actor. He was cast to play [[Rock Hudson]] in the [[Netflix]] series, ''[[Hollywood (American TV series)|Hollywood]]'' (2020).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/dylan-mcdermott-samara-weaving-jim-parsons-maude-apatow-joe-mantello-ryan-murphy-netflix-series-hollywood-1202746400/|title=\u2018Hollywood\u2019: Dylan McDermott, Samara Weaving, Jim Parsons, Maude Apatow & Joe Mantello Among Netflix Series Cast Additions|last=Petski|first=Nellie Andreeva,Denise|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-09-27|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17|last3=Petski|first3=Denise}}</ref> He is best known for playing the role of [[Sean Collier]] in ''[[Patriots Day (film)|Patriots Day]]'' (2016).<ref>{{cite news|last=Sweeney|first=Emily|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2016/05/05/jake-picking-joins-patriots-day-cast/wLNEaEMyUfEKaj5kQM3izN/story.html|title=Jake Picking joins \u2018Patriots Day\u2019 cast|newspaper=[[Boston Globe]]|date=2016-05-05|accessdate=2018-03-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Cappadona|first=Bryanna|url=https://www.boston.com/culture/movies/2016/05/05/patriots-day-sean-collier-jake-picking-tamerlan-tsarnaev-wife-melissa-benoist|title=Boston Marathon bombings movie casts actors for MIT Officer Sean Collier, Tamerlan Tsarnaev\u2019s wife|newspaper=[[Boston Globe]]|date=2016-05-05|accessdate=2018-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable